docs.lead_paragraph: THE CHOLERA CASES IN PHILADELPHIA.--The weekly report of the Board of Health, of the interments during the past week, gives nine deaths from Cholera. Some excitable persons fancied that the city was about to be ravaged by disease, and no little alarm has been created among the timid.

docs.lead_paragraph: To the Editor of the New-York Daily Times: The stockholders and the public are not likely to be satisfied with the anonymous communications from the attorney of this Company, who, instead of answering the charges made against them, writes as follows: "But one person out of the Board of Directors has access to the documents he promulgates." That is certainly remarkable.

headline.main: The Board of Health and Cholera.

docs.lead_paragraph: Judging from the fact that there were twelve fewer fatal cases of cholera last week than the week proceeding, and from the improved appearance of many streets, the Board of Health did good service to the City last week.
docs.snippet: Judging from the fact that there were twelve fewer fatal cases of cholera last week than the week proceeding, and from the improved appearance of many streets, the Board of Health did good service to the City last week.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Board of Health reports nine cases of Cholera during last week. One death from the same disease occurred to-day in the County Prison, where seven females, prisoners, have been attacked during the past week. No cases heard of to-day. Total mortality for the week in the city, 222.
